h are wrappers around NDArrayBackedExtensionArray). The linregress function performs least-squares regression computation on the input arrays, producing statistical results (slope, intercept, p-value, etc.). This demonstrates how scipy consumes aggregated and structured array data from the upstream numpy and pandas layers to perform domain-specific scientific computations.\n\n## Data Flow Architecture\nThe complete data flow chain is: **raw ndarray creation (numpy/numpy) → aggregation operations like sum() → wrapped in pandas extension arrays (pandas-dev/pandas) → consumed by scipy statistical functions (scipy/scipy)**. This architecture allows scientific Python applications to (1) create and aggregate numerical data efficiently in numpy, (2) organize and manipulate that data at scale in pandas using familiar tabular interfaces, and (3) apply sophisticated statistical and scientific computations in scipy while maintaining seamless interoperability across all three layers.\n"
